AOC

This module contains some modules that help with generic problems of Advent of Code puzzles.
* The Input module, provides ways to load the puzzle input in different formats, and return it as a single array
(or scalar).
* the Point module helps with moving through a grid using a (x,y) coordinates.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Build.PL
	./Build
	./Build test
	./Build install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc AOC

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker (report bugs here)
        https://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=AOC

    CPAN Ratings
        https://cpanratings.perl.org/d/AOC

    Search CPAN
        https://metacpan.org/release/AOC


